1. System Architecture

The system follows a modular machine learning pipeline:

Data Collection

Data Cleaning

Exploratory Data Analysis

Feature Engineering

Model Training

Model Evaluation

Model Serialization

Flask Deployment

Cloud Hosting (Render)

Architecture Flow:

User Input → Flask App → Load Model (.pkl) → Prediction → Probability Output → Display Result

2. Data Preprocessing

The dataset was cleaned and prepared using the following steps:

Removed duplicate records

Handled missing values

Converted categorical features using One-Hot Encoding

Converted TotalCharges to numeric

Separated features (X) and target (y)

Target Variable:
Churn (1 = Yes, 0 = No)

3. Feature Engineering

Applied:

One-Hot Encoding using pandas.get_dummies()

Feature alignment using feature_columns.pkl

Train-test split (80-20)

Standardization (if applied)

4. Model Selection

Since churn prediction is a binary classification problem, the following models were considered:

Logistic Regression

Random Forest (optional if tried)

Decision Tree (optional)

Final Selected Model:
Logistic Regression (balanced class weight)

Reason:

Interpretable

Fast

Good ROC-AUC performance

5. Model Evaluation

Evaluation metrics used:

Accuracy

Precision

Recall

F1 Score

ROC-AUC Score

Confusion Matrix

ROC Curve was plotted to evaluate model discrimination ability.

6. Model Serialization

The trained model was saved using:

joblib.dump(model, "churn_model.pkl")

Feature columns were saved using:

joblib.dump(feature_columns, "feature_columns.pkl")

This ensures consistent prediction during deployment.

7. Deployment Architecture

Deployment stack:

Frontend: HTML + CSS
Backend: Flask
Model Serving: Gunicorn
Cloud Hosting: Render

Procfile used:

web: gunicorn app:app

Root Directory: deployment

8. Limitations

Model performance depends on dataset quality

No real-time streaming data

Limited feature selection

9. Future Improvements

Use advanced ensemble models

Add SHAP explainability

Add database integration

Add dashboard analytics

Use Docker for containerization